Apple promised us years ago that AI could flexibly integrate many different functions on your phone (finally coming to fruition on Android, I hear). 

Why the delay?

I think the answer is... cost!

The latest frontier models have proven that agentic applications can work very robustly. Most developers and hobbyists are using their Claude Max/Codex subscription to run the agents. When you ship, you need to pay API prices. You quickly realise that even doing basic stuff can rack up 50 dollars in less than an hour, for a single user.

I think this is why so many developers rave about how amazing generative AI is. They build really cool applications, but they never ship them.
